1. Every time create "new" object in any function of a class, make sure to delete it in the destructor of that class

EeDistributionCreator::~EeDistributionCreator(){
   delete kXSecMatrix_PDG14;
   delete kXSecMatrix_PDGminus14;
   delete kXSecMatrix_PDG12;
   delete kXSecMatrix_PDGminus12;

}

2. For raw pointers, delete the old objects before using new to point the pointer at something else, since it will be a memory
leak due to the fact that the only pointer pointing at that object will now be pointing at something else

3. Initialize the raw pointers to be nullptr since deleting it will be safe in that case

